The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                      
	Amardeep Ekka scored a brace as East Coast Railway beat Calcutta Customs 5-2 in the Coal India 113th All-India Beighton Cup hockey tournament at SAI Eastern India Sports Complex on Friday.      
	In the days other match, ERSA defeated Mumbai XI 5-3 (1-1) via tie-breaker.          
	 East Bengal coach Subhas Bhowmick on Friday met club officials to put forth a few suggestions. According to sources, the newly-appointed East Bengal coach wants to practise twice daily from Monday.       
	The coach also wants to shift practice from the club ground, which is undergoing renovation, to the Howrah stadium.                
	 150 players will take part in the Treat Joosi BTA AITA Championship Series which will begin at the Bengal Tennis Association complex from Saturday. The main draw matches will be played from Monday. The qualifying matches will be played on Saturday and Sunday.       
	In the U-18 section, Bengals Bibaswan Deb and Amrita Mukherjee start as favourite for boys and girls respectively.                
	 The District Level Sports meet of primary schools will be held at the Rabindra Sarobar Stadium on Tuesday.           
	Golf: Junior meet at Tollygunge Club      
	Hockey: Beighton Cup at SAI complex from 12.45 pm.      
	Tennis: AITA championship at BTA complex.                                                                                                                                                                       
